        "created_at": "2026-01-13T12:09:32.535Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It has been a while but it always bothers me when it happens. When I receive a Signal voice or video call, Signal takes over my entire screen. It stops me from doing anything else on my phone until I choose to accept or decline the call. When I receive a normal phone call however (not Signal) I can simply tap the lock button on my phone and the ringing stops (it also never takes over my entire screen).</p>\n<p>I would love an ignore option on any calls or at least have signal behave the same way that a normal phone call works.</p>",
