        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-13T20:06:53.999Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"desert_nip\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"74195\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> desert_nip:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>As far as I can see, the caller can’t see whether the call was declined or ignored, only the recipient can. So you might as well just hang up. :)</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I have to partially correct myself here: While the message in the chat doesn’t say which of the two it was, the other person could still notice in the moment that the “ringing” ended early if you hung up.</p>",
