        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/4af34b/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-13T20:18:17.686Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Okay, I just used a friend’s phone, and I need to make a retraction. It looks like Signal does NOT lock your screen now (although I could have sworn it did just a few months back). So, I’ll just close this thread (or someone else who can).</p>\n<p>edit: It used to lock your screen until you answered and any time you entered the app it took you straight to the call, and the and you couldn’t use the phone’s UI to exit.</p>\n<p>edit2: although, if people think there is value in allowing Signal to let the caller’s side to ‘ring‘ after a decline, I will leave it up.</p>",
